.TH "mech" "1" "2026-02-08"
.PP
.SH NAME
.PP
mech - browse and interact with HyperMap resources
.PP
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\fBmech\fR start [-f|--foreground]
.PP
\fBmech\fR stop
.PP
\fBmech\fR open <url> [--name <name>]
.PP
\fBmech\fR show <tab[:path]>
.PP
\fBmech\fR set <tab:path> <value>
.PP
\fBmech\fR use <tab:path> [key=value .\&.\&.\&]
.PP
\fBmech\fR fork <tab> [--name <name>]
.PP
\fBmech\fR close <tab>
.PP
\fBmech\fR name <tab> <name>
.PP
\fBmech\fR tabs
.PP
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\fBmech\fR is a command-line client for browsing and interacting with HyperMap
resources.\& HyperMap is a hypermedia format that exposes structured data and
controls (actions) which can be navigated and triggered programmatically.\&
.PP
\fBmech\fR communicates with a background daemon (\fBmechd\fR) over a Unix socket.\& The
daemon must be started before any other commands will work.\&
.PP
.SH COMMANDS
.PP
.SS Daemon
.PP
\fBstart\fR [-f|--foreground]
.RS 4
Start the daemon.\& With \fB-f\fR, run in the foreground instead of
daemonizing.\& The client will wait up to 3 seconds for the daemon to
become ready.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBstop\fR
.RS 4
Stop the daemon and clean up its socket and PID files.\&
.PP
.RE
.SS Tabs
.PP
\fBopen\fR <url> [--name <name>]
.RS 4
Open a URL in a new tab.\& Optionally assign a name for easier reference.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBtabs\fR
.RS 4
List all open tabs with their indices and names.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBclose\fR <tab>
.RS 4
Close a tab.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBname\fR <tab> <name>
.RS 4
Name or rename a tab.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBfork\fR <tab> [--name <name>]
.RS 4
Duplicate a tab, creating a copy of its current state.\& Useful for
preserving state before making changes or for exploring alternatives.\&
.PP
.RE
.SS Viewing and Interacting
.PP
\fBshow\fR <tab[:path]>
.RS 4
Display the contents of a tab, optionally narrowed to a specific path.\&
Output is colorized when writing to a terminal.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBset\fR <tab:path> <value>
.RS 4
Set a value at a path without triggering any control.\& Used for filling
in form fields before submission.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBuse\fR <tab:path> [key=value .\&.\&.\&]
.RS 4
Trigger a control at the given path.\& Optionally pass form data as
key=value pairs inline.\& This is the primary way to navigate and submit
actions.\&
.PP
.RE
.SH TAB REFERENCES
.PP
Tabs are referenced by index or by name:
.PP
.PD 0
.IP \(bu 4
\fBIndex\fR: the order in which tabs were opened, starting at 1.\&
.IP \(bu 4
\fBName\fR: a label assigned with \fB--name\fR or the \fBname\fR command.\&
.PD
.PP
A tab reference can include a path, separated by a colon:
.PP
.RS 4
1:market/ibm/price
stocks:nav/home
.PP
.RE
.SH PATHS
.PP
HyperMap content is hierarchical.\& Paths use \fB/\fR as a separator:
.PP
.RS 4
market
market/ibm
market/ibm/price
.PP
.RE
.SH OUTPUT FORMAT
.PP
The \fBshow\fR command renders HyperMap content as an indented tree.\& Each line is
one of:
.PP
\fBkey: value\fR
.RS 4
A leaf node with a scalar value (string, number, boolean, or null).\&
.PP
.RE
\fBkey/\fR
.RS 4
A container with children.\& The trailing \fB/\fR indicates nesting below.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBkey@\fR
.RS 4
A control — an interactive element that can be triggered with \fBmech use\fR.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBkey@/\fR
.RS 4
A control that also has children (e.\&g.\&, a form with input fields).\&
.PP
.RE
\fB[N]\fR
.RS 4
An array element at index N.\& May have a value or children.\&
.PP
.RE
Children are indented under their parent.\& The \fB#\fR metadata key is hidden from
output.\&
.PP
Example:
.PP
.nf
.RS 4
nav/
  home@
  stocks@
market/
  ibm/
    ticker: IBM
    price: 142\&.50
    submitOrder@/
      quantity: 0
      submit@
.fi
.RE
.PP
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.PP
\fBMECH_SOCKET_PATH\fR
.RS 4
Path to the Unix domain socket used for client-daemon communication.\&
Default: \fI/tmp/mech.\&sock\fR
.PP
.RE
\fBMECH_PID_PATH\fR
.RS 4
Path to the daemon PID file.\& Default: \fI/tmp/mech.\&pid\fR
.PP
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Start the daemon and open a resource:
.PP
.nf
.RS 4
mech start
mech open https://example\&.com/ --name main
mech show main
.fi
.RE
.PP
Navigate using a control, then view the result:
.PP
.nf
.RS 4
mech use main:nav/stocks
mech show main
.fi
.RE
.PP
Fill a form field, then submit:
.PP
.nf
.RS 4
mech set main:market/ibm/submitOrder/quantity 100
mech use main:market/ibm/submitOrder/submit
mech show main
.fi
.RE
.PP
Or submit with inline values:
.PP
.nf
.RS 4
mech use main:market/ibm/submitOrder quantity=100
.fi
.RE
.PP
Fork a tab before making changes:
.PP
.nf
.RS 4
mech fork main --name backup
mech use main:market/ibm/submitOrder quantity=100
.fi
.RE
.PP
Clean up:
.PP
.nf
.RS 4
mech close main
mech stop
.fi
.RE
